Four of the lions were captured on Tuesday near the N4 highway in the Mananga area and have been returned to the park. JOHANNESBURG - The Mpumalanga Tourism and Parks Authority (MTPA) says the fifth lion that escaped from the Kruger National Park has still not been located.Four of the lions were captured on Tuesday near the N4 highway in the Mananga area and have been returned to the park.Residents are being urged to remain vigilant.MTPA spokesperson Kholofelo Nkambule said: Currently, the search is still ongoing with regards to the one lion that has not been found. We think that it might have moved to the park or roaming around somewhere but we will continue to search. 